 but 15% is a fail. Anything else is pure delusion and gerrymandering of the league table positions, and helps no-one other than the school, who get to say &quot;hey, none of our kids are failing*&quot; &#10;*Where a fail is a failure to turn up for the exam."/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="552" language="en" documentId="842" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="TheMackenator" date="07 January 2011 8:11pm" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/9058668" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="842" notes="" title="Why I home school my children"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="500"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="501" end="552"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43"/></xmi:XMI>